h5. Issue Summary

We have this documentation with regards Service ID '*******' no longer exists: https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirakb/service-id-xxxxx-no-longer-exists-773981355.html/

When a user experiencing the problem described in the article attempts to apply the diagnosis on the database, they would find that the table *clusteredjob* does not have any column called *trigger_name*.

h5. Verification

Query the JIRA database with the following query:
{code}
select * from clusteredjob where trigger_name like '%<Service_ID>%';
{code}

h5. Expected Result

JIRA would show a result with the entry specified.

h5. Actual Result

JIRA would throw an error that the column in question does not exist as seen below:

{code}
ERROR:  column "trigger_name" does not exist
LINE 1: select * from clusteredjob where trigger_name like '10000';
                                         ^
********** Error **********
{code}

h5. Fix

Update this query to reference the *job_id* instead

{code}
select * from clusteredjob where job_id like '%<Service_ID>%';
{code}

(!) *The above is for JIRA Server only and we would recommend confirming with Atlassian support before running any queries on your database if possible*

h3. Problem
Searching for a Confluence page when creating a new issue link fails to display list of all spaces. 
Search in all spaces is unaffected - meaning: it will indeed search for pages in all spaces.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Open a JIRA issue;
# Choose *More > Link*;
# Select *Confluence page*;
# Click *search for a page*;
# Open the dropdown list to select a space;

h3. Expected Behavior
All spaces should be displayed in the select-list when linking a page to an issue.

h3. Actual Behavior
Only the first 25 spaces are shown, because there is no pagination implemented on the select-list and the request passes {{maxResults=25}}.

h3. Workaround
There is no workaround available at this time for searching inside spaces.

In JIM, the {{jira-importers-plugin-tests}} module uses a very old version of the JIRA REST Java client:

{code}<dependency>
        <groupId>com.atlassian.jira</groupId>
        <artifactId>jira-rest-java-client</artifactId>
        <version>1.0</version>
</dependency>{code}

The rest of JIRA is using version 4.0.0 of these replacement artifacts:
* {{jira-rest-java-client-api}}
* {{jira-rest-java-client-core}}

We should change the above JIM module to use the newer version and make any necessary code changes, noting that it's a jump of three major versions.
